<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-6669] Compile in groovyConsole instantiates class</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6669</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Probably not serious, but put this in groovyConsole and compile&#226;&#128;&#166;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;OtherThing {
    OtherThing() {
        def v = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;
        v.hashCode()
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You&apos;ll get an NPE for the v.hashCode() line. If you add another statement before the class def (e.g. def c = null) it doesn&apos;t happen.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Weird.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
